President Biden held a meeting with a group of governors and mayors from both political parties to discuss the COVID-19 plan and their needs and recommendations. The American Rescue Plan, which includes providing support to states in dealing with the virus and helping them economically, was a key topic of discussion. The President acknowledged the challenges faced by these leaders on the frontlines and emphasized the role of the federal government in addressing the crisis. He expressed his interest in hearing their opinions on the recovery plan and what they need the most. President Biden highlighted the importance of governors and mayors in dealing with the crisis and their firsthand experience in their respective states and cities. The meeting aimed to gather insights and perspectives from these leaders to inform future actions.